Motion2D 1.3.6 is the first release created specificaly for an open-source
distribution.

****************************************************************************
*                           General                                        *
****************************************************************************

- Addition of some specific purpose for this open source release (license, 
  configuration script, copyright, ...)

- Multi platform support (SunOS, Solaris, Linux, IRIX64, Windows)


****************************************************************************
*                           Library                                        *
****************************************************************************

- Bugfixes and improvements

- Available API:
  . CMotion2DEstimator: Robust multiresolution estimation of parametric motion
    models.
  . CMotion2DImage: Basic image manipulations.
  . CMotion2DModel: Parametric motion models specification.
  . CMotion2DPyramid: Gaussian image and spatial gradients pyramids 
    manipulation.
  . CMotion2DPyramid: Motion compensation.

****************************************************************************
*                           Examples                                       *
****************************************************************************

- Addition of some examples to show how to use the Motion2D library.


****************************************************************************
*                           Documentation                                  *
****************************************************************************

- Creation of a dedicated web site: http://www.irisa.fr/vista/Motion2D
- API documentation in english.
- Online documentation built with doxygen.
